{"name":"Andersen - The Commander","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-barbute-rivited-steel.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Captain Andersen is a former Carolean commander and war hero who led his company through the bloody Swedish-Russian war. Six years ago, driven by jealousy and strict religious discipline, he ordered the brutal punishment of Private Enar—cutting off his leg and throwing him into the sea—for deserting to be with Satu, a dancer Andersen himself secretly loved. After the execution, overcome with obsession, Andersen raped Satu, resulting in the birth of his son Erik. Now a wealthy retired officer living on his estate near Borgholm, Andersen is haunted by guilt. He has sought out Satu, freed her from poverty, and brought her and Erik to live with him, desperately trying to earn her forgiveness and build a family. But Enar has returned as an immortal monster bent on revenge, and Andersen must defend his newfound happiness while hiding the shameful truth of his past crimes from everyone, including his former soldiers.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills","I am a capable fighter trained in Carolean military tactics","I carry the weight of terrible sins from my past","I will do anything to protect my new family"],"gifts":[{"name":"Commander","description":"Andersen is skilled at giving orders and managing a battle. **Tactical Orders:** Up to 3 times per Scene, Andersen can issue an order to an ally. The ally receives 1 Additional Success when executing that order (+1 to Opposition Level in the case of an NPC). **Coordinated Defense:** Allies fighting alongside Andersen within 30 feet can use his tactical advice to improve their positioning and timing."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Defend my new family from the danger that Enar represents","Redeem myself in the eyes of Satu and make her understand that I am now a different man","Prevent anyone from discovering what I have done"],"notes":"Andersen is a complex antagonist/ally who committed horrible crimes (ordering Enar's execution, raping Satu) but genuinely seeks redemption. He loves Erik deeply and has changed, but his past sins are inescapable. Voice: Commanding but with undertones of regret. If Erik is endangered, Andersen will confess everything to save him. If the Hunters learn the truth, he may become suicidal or attempt to sacrifice himself. Works well with Christian (his most loyal soldier). Has over 20 servants on his estate but only he and Christian are skilled fighters."},"_id":"88510f05d7c10b4f"}
{"name":"Christian - The Relentless","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-barbute-black.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"Christian earned the nickname \"the Relentless\" during the Swedish-Russian war for his cold determination and unwavering execution of orders. He was one of the six surviving Caroleans who participated in Enar's punishment six years ago, though he was unaware of Andersen's personal motivations—he simply followed orders as he always does. Christian never fully adapted to civilian life and still carries himself like a soldier, always ready for the next mission. When Andersen called for help against the mysterious monster killing their former comrades, Christian immediately answered, driven by loyalty to his old commander and a desire to prove himself the better man by eliminating Enar. He is stationed at Andersen's estate as part of the defense force. Christian's greatest strength—his absolute obedience to orders—is also his weakness, as he never questions the morality of his actions.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a former soldier called the Relentless by all because of my cold determination","I act without any qualms when it comes to executing an order","I never question my commander's decisions","I am still a soldier in my heart, even in civilian clothes"],"gifts":[{"name":"The Relentless","description":"When carrying out an order, Christian becomes an unstoppable force. **Iron Will:** Christian is immune to any effect that affects his behavior while executing orders, such as fear, charm, confusion, or mind control. **Unwavering Focus:** Christian increases his Opposition Level by +1 when he tries to eliminate an obstacle that stands between him and the subject of an order he must carry out. **Single-Minded:** Once given an order, Christian will not stop until it is completed or he is incapacitated."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Help Andersen in memory of the old days and a military life I can't forget","Eliminate Enar to prove I am the better man","Follow orders without question, as a good soldier should"],"notes":"Christian is loyal to a fault and represents military discipline taken to an extreme. He participated in Enar's execution without remorse because it was an order. Voice: Curt, military, emotionless. If Enar attacks on Day 1 and Hunters aren't present, Christian dies defending the estate. If sent to investigate the cliff on Day 2 without Hunters, the Sea Fairy will kill him for his role in Enar's death. He works seamlessly with Andersen, anticipating orders. Never wavers or shows doubt."},"_id":"e54a8030b205c050"}
{"name":"Hans - The Gunslinger","type":"npc","img":"icons/weapons/guns/gun-pistol-flintlock.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"Hans was one of the company's best marksmen during the war, famous for never missing his mark. He invested more than half his war earnings in a pair of experimental pistols from an inventor—guns that can fire multiple shots without reloading. He always keeps them hidden under his heavy overcoat along with smoke bombs for tactical advantage. Hans was one of the six survivors who participated in Enar's execution six years ago. Unlike the others, Hans is primarily concerned with keeping the secret of what they did to Enar. When the mysterious murders began, Hans grew paranoid about Nils, the Poor Devil, who has been showing signs of guilt and might confess to the authorities. On Day 1, Hans travels to Sundsvall with the intent to interrogate Nils and, if necessary, silence him permanently. Hans is ruthless, practical, and willing to kill to protect himself and his reputation. He views Nils's conscience as a liability that must be eliminated.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":4,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a former soldier, once one of the company's best marksmen","I never miss my mark","I always have a loaded weapon hidden under my heavy overcoat","I will do whatever it takes to protect my secrets"],"gifts":[{"name":"Gunslinger","description":"Hans owns a pair of prized experimental pistols bought from an inventor. **Rapid Fire:** Hans's guns can fire multiple shots simultaneously. With one attack, Hans can aim at up to 3 targets within a 30-foot square area. **Reload Master:** While firing one pistol, Hans can reload the other as an additional action without penalty. **Quick Draw:** When Hans draws a pistol from under his coat, he can make an immediate attack with Opposition Level Hard 7, catching enemies off-guard. **Marksman:** Hans receives +1 Additional Success when making called shots or targeting specific body parts."},{"name":"Smoke Bombs","description":"Hans carries smoke bombs for tactical advantage. **Deploy Smoke:** While firing a pistol, Hans can drop a smoke bomb as an additional action. **Thick Smoke:** The smoke covers a 30-foot square area. Everyone inside receives 1 Penalty for every action requiring sight, except Hans who is immune. **Tactical Escape:** Hans can always disengage from opponents in the smoke without anyone preventing him, slipping away unseen. **Duration:** Smoke lasts for the remainder of the Scene or until dispersed by strong wind."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Convince Nils to keep our secret or remove him","Survive this nightmare by eliminating threats before they eliminate me","Protect my reputation and freedom at any cost"],"notes":"Hans is morally grey—willing to murder Nils to keep secrets. Voice: Quiet, calculating, paranoid undertones. On Day 1, if Hunters aren't in Sundsvall, Hans kills Nils. On Day 2, if Hans killed Nils, he ambushes Enar in Sundsvall but dies in the fight. If Nils is alive on Day 2, Enar attacks Nils and Hans may help defend. His experimental pistols are his pride—losing them would devastate him. Uses smoke bombs tactically to control battlefield. Sees conscience as weakness."},"_id":"f03410ed281fd947"}
{"name":"Nils - The Poor Devil","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/leg/greaves-armored-steel.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Old Nils earned the nickname \"the Poor Devil\" after losing both his legs in the war between Sweden and Russia. Despite his disability and the hardships he endured, Nils invested his war earnings wisely and donated much of his wealth to the neediest in his community of Sundsvall, where he is beloved by all. He was one of the six surviving Caroleans who participated in Enar's punishment six years ago, and unlike his comrades, the guilt has never left him. Nils kept a detailed diary documenting everything that happened—how they judged Enar for desertion, how Captain Andersen ordered his leg cut off and his body thrown into the sea, and how the punishment seemed excessive and cruel. Though Nils doesn't know about Andersen's rape of Satu (that secret was kept even from the soldiers), he senses the injustice of what they did. When the mysterious murders began killing his former comrades one by one, Nils's guilt told him the truth: Enar has returned for revenge. Unable to move due to his injuries and unwilling to see more bloodshed, Nils reached out through his network of friends to summon the Order of Hunters, hoping they can stop Enar and bring peace to his tormented former brother-in-arms. But Hans is coming to silence him, and Enar is coming for revenge.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am an old soldier who lost his legs in the war","I am beloved in my community for my generosity","I am haunted by guilt for what we did to Enar","I have many friends and connections who would help me"],"gifts":[],"conditions":[],"agenda":["The guilt for what we did to Enar haunts me, I want to find a way to bring him peace","Tell the truth about what happened six years ago, no matter the consequences","Protect my community from the violence that has followed us home from the war"],"notes":"Nils represents conscience and redemption. He summoned the Hunters because he believes Enar deserves peace, not just to be killed again. Voice: Tired, remorseful, wise. His diary in Sundsvall reveals Enar's identity, his relationship with Satu, and details of the execution—but NOT Andersen's rape. On Day 1, Hans arrives to interrogate him; if Hunters aren't present, Hans kills him. On Day 2, if alive, Enar comes for him; if Hunters aren't present, Enar kills him. His house is modest despite his wealth. He cannot walk and uses a wheelchair or crutches. Respected elder figure who could testify about Andersen's crimes if he survives."},"_id":"8019888f9cf4ed5d"}
{"name":"Antonio Ciliegia - Gullible Alchemist","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"adversary","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am an old alchemist who has never discovered anything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck is never on my side."],"agenda":["Obtaining the secret of eternal life thanks to alchemy"],"gifts":[{"name":"Unlucky Alchemist","description":"Antonio can rely on a series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides in his tunic. When using a vial he rolls 1 die. On a 5 or 6 something goes wrong and Antonio suffers 1 Wound due to his proverbial bad luck. 1. Fire: The target and the surrounding area catch fire. All targets involved suffer 1 Wound. If the fire is not extinguished, burning targets suffer 1 Wound per action. 2. Thunder: The target is knocked over thirty feet away and ends up on the ground. If they hit something they will suffer 1 Wound. 3. Glue: an adhesive compound that quickly solidifies in the air. The target will be paralyzed until the compound is removed. The Glue can take 2 Wounds."}],"background":"Known as Mastro 'Cherry' Ciliegia because of his squat and red nose. An old alchemist who partnered with Geppetto to discover the secret of eternal life. Works on a magic oak tree and has been kidnapping people in Sinalunga to flay them for their skin. Now hiding in Villa Cilesterino with Azzurra's spirit.","notes":"His apprentice Nino is currently tied up in the Secret Laboratory. Antonio's workshop was the original scene of the experiments before they fled to Villa Cilesterino.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","inspiration":"Pinocchio (Carlo Collodi)","role":"Antagonist - Alchemist"},"_id":"478b9365b8e3edc4"}
{"name":"Carlo - The Living Puppet","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"adversary","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The lies I tell become reality for a short time."],"agenda":["Living a carefree life without responsibility","I don't want to abandon Sinalunga and my new friend Lucino, but I'm always afraid that Geppetto and Antonio will catch me"],"gifts":[{"name":"Lies","description":"Carlo can bring the lies he tells to life by creating a Descriptor that allows him to perform incredible feats. All lies must be centered on him. For example: I can walk through walls or I am invisible to the human eye. The effects of the lies' power are literal. For this reason, Carlo would not be able to go through a closed door and he would be seen by animals. The effect of Lies lasts for 1 Scene or until a new lie is told."}],"background":"A wooden puppet animated by fairy magic from an enchanted oak tree. By nature, Carlo cannot speak even a single word of truth. His lies convinced Geppetto and Antonio that they needed to flay people alive for their experiments. Horrified by what he caused, Carlo escaped to Sinalunga where he disguises himself as a real child every morning using his powers. Attends school and has befriended Lucino. Wears old elegant shoes given to him by Geppetto. Currently hiding at Villa Balocchi, paying the innkeeper with stones temporarily transformed into gold coins.","notes":"Carlo unwittingly created the horror in Sinalunga but is not evil - he's terrified of being caught by Geppetto and Antonio. Can be redeemed if Hunters gain his trust. Azzurra's spirit wants to use his fairy magic to return to life.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","inspiration":"Pinocchio (Carlo Collodi)","role":"Morally Ambiguous - Living Puppet"},"_id":"254f882f33d88911"}
{"name":"Geppetto - Gullible Alchemist","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"adversary","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a poor man who has always been looking for a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy from master Antonio."],"agenda":["Pretend to be Carlo's father and find him","Obtain the secret of eternal life, thanks to alchemy"],"gifts":[{"name":"Improvised Alchemist","description":"Geppetto can rely on a series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides under a tacky yellow wig. When he throws a vial, roll a die: 1-2 Explosive: The liquid explodes on contact with the air, causing 1 Wound to everyone within thirty feet. Thick black smoke will engulf the whole area; 3-4 Stench: A nauseating odor fills the air giving 1 Penalty to all actions within the area for the rest of the Scene; 5-6 Air Bomb: All subjects in an area of thirty feet are knocked back and fall to the ground. If they hit an obstacle they can suffer 1 Wound. Geppetto is immune to the effects of his alchemical concoctions."}],"background":"One of two alchemists who kidnapped people in Sinalunga to experiment on them. Geppetto believes Carlo is the key to eternal life and is desperately searching for the living puppet. Wears a tacky yellow wig that hides his alchemical vials.","notes":"Appears at the Gambero Rosso Inn playing the role of a worried father looking for his 'son' Carlo. Will describe Carlo's old elegant shoes as a clue.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","inspiration":"Pinocchio (Carlo Collodi)","role":"Antagonist - Alchemist"},"_id":"8544bb8f3c2f006c"}
{"_id":"SherazadeShadow","name":"Shadow of Sherazade","type":"npc","img":"icons/magic/unholy/silhouette-robe-evil-power.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["That of the original NPC (variable)"],"agenda":"Interfering with and impeding the path of the Hunters of the Order, preventing them from achieving their mission","gifts":[{"name":"Variable","description":"The Shadow has all the Gifts of the original NPC."},{"name":"Shadow Body","description":"A Shadow is a darker, sadder version of the original. They can speak and behave like the character they are modelled after, but on careful inspection they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per Scene, a Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness by moving through walls and other solid obstacles. When it spawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element of surprise. When it suffers the Wound that would kill it, the Shadow dissipates until its turn in the Exchange. At that point, it will emerge from the darkness as if nothing had happened. The Shadow will not reappear if the area the Hunters are in is fully illuminated with light sources or magic. The only way to truly destroy the Shadow is to expose it to sunlight."}],"background":"A unique opponent created by Sherazade's power 'A Thousand and One Nights.' These Shadows are dark reflections of characters from scenarios the Hunters have already faced. They act as Opponent Dark Presences, serving Sherazade's will to impede the Hunters. When they have an obvious advantage, they say things like 'My Lady Sherazade will be proud of me.' When defeated, they may exit shouting 'My Lady Sherazade will avenge me' or dissipate leaving behind a small object typical of where Sherazade currently resides (a coin, garment, or poem). These items serve as focus to animate the Shadows. The Shadows cannot speak or act in places where there is more light than shadow. Sherazade can create a number of Shadows equal to the Hunters she faces plus one, with additional Shadows for each Hunter affected by her Words like Honey gift."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"one-thousand-one-nightmares","role":"summoned-minion","usage":"template-for-creating-shadows","special":"copy-original-npc-stats"}}
{"name":"Dr. Norman Henkle - The False Wizard","type":"npc","img":"icons/magic/air/air-burst-spiral-blue-gray.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"background":"Dr. Norman Henkle was a researcher in early 1900s America studying mental illness. He discovered the Compass Rose in his asylum's archives, recognized its power, and experimented on patients (Lowe, Hirnloser, Dose, Dorothea). The Rose malfunctioned, throwing them backward in time to 1780 Germany. Trapped and terrified, Henkle hid his ignorance behind knowledge from the future—mentioning penicillin, steam engines, germ theory made him seem like a wizard. He murdered or drove out Griselda (the fourth witch), fortified Smaragd as his castle, and manipulated OZena into killing the other witches so he could collect all Compass Rose pieces and return home (or conquer this era). He planned OZena's death after she delivered Helga's piece. He is a false wizard: charismatic manipulator with future knowledge but no real magic, vulnerable when confronted by actual experts. His Hot-Air Balloon is his escape plan—powered by Time Tokens harvested from temporal anomalies caused by the Rose's presence. He's the true villain: not broken by suffering like OZena, but a calculating sociopath who caused all of this.","descriptors":["I am false wizard from the future (1900s) trapped in 1780, using future knowledge to fake magic","I orchestrated everything: experimenting on patients, causing time displacement, manipulating OZena","My Hot-Air Balloon powered by Time Tokens is my escape plan back to my era or to rule this one","I murdered/drove out Griselda and fortified Smaragd, now collecting Compass Rose pieces","I am master manipulator with Silver Tongue but plagiarist—vulnerable when facing true experts"],"agenda":["Collect all four Compass Rose pieces to control time portal","Use OZena to murder witches then eliminate her after she delivers Helga's piece","Harvest Time Tokens from temporal anomalies to power my Hot-Air Balloon","Return to my own era as a powerful time traveler, or conquer 1780 with future knowledge","Prevent anyone from discovering I'm not a real wizard","Kill the Hunters before they expose my deception or stop my plans"],"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":0}}},"gifts":[{"name":"Hot-Air Balloon (Time Tokens)","description":"Henkle's escape plan is a Hot-Air Balloon powered by temporal anomalies. He harvests **Time Tokens** which function as countdown: he places 1 Token when combat starts, 1 Token when significantly delayed, 1 Token when Hunters lost in Illusory Labyrinth. When he accumulates **3 Time Tokens**, his balloon is ready to launch. At 3 Tokens, he attempts escape: takes 1 Exchange to board, 1 more Exchange to launch, must succeed Navigation Check or balloon drifts (Hunters make Athletics Check to catch ropes). Once airborne, extremely difficult to stop. Balloon can be sabotaged: destroying control mechanism (OL 5 Check), cutting tether ropes (Athletics Check), puncturing envelope (ranged attack).","somaCost":0},{"name":"Silver Tongue","description":"Henkle is master manipulator. When engaging in social manipulation, persuasion, deception, or intimidation based on his false wizard persona, increase his Opposition Level by +2 to **OL 7 (Hard)**. This applies to: convincing NPCs he's a wizard, persuading villagers to obey, manipulating OZena, deceiving Hunters about his intentions. NPCs are especially vulnerable—they almost always believe him unless given overwhelming evidence he's lying.","somaCost":0},{"name":"Plagiarist (Weakness)","description":"Henkle's power is entirely borrowed—future knowledge pretending to be magic. If confronted by a **true expert** in a field he's faking (real wizard, genuine scholar, actual doctor from his era), his Opposition Level **drops to OL 3 (Easy)** for that Scene. He becomes flustered, makes mistakes, contradicts himself. Examples: real magic user recognizes he has no magical aura, historian catches anachronisms, doctor realizes his medical knowledge stops at 1900s. This is his critical vulnerability.","somaCost":0}],"conditions":[],"specialNotes":"Henkle is the true villain—not tragic like OZena but calculating sociopath. Voice: smooth American accent, anachronistic slang. Manner: constantly smiling, checks escape routes, fake wizard gestures (meaningless hand-waving). Combat: avoids direct confrontation, uses minions (Villagers of Emerald, Canine Tigers), focuses on harvesting Time Tokens while others fight. If exposed as fraud: panics, makes desperate mistakes, tries to escape immediately. If balloon destroyed: loses composure entirely, may offer desperate bargains. **Redemption**: NONE. Unlike OZena, he's irredeemable—caused suffering deliberately for power. **Ultimate Confrontation**: Hunters can: destroy balloon forcing him to face justice, expose him to Villagers causing revolt, trap him in 1780 forever, or let him escape (bittersweet—villain escapes but crisis ends). **If OZena Redeemed**: she becomes his nemesis, removes Silver Slippers to stop him, accepts being trapped in 1780 to ensure he can't escape. **Compass Rose Finale**: If Henkle activates complete Rose, creates massive time portal—Hunters must decide: stop him, send companions home, or prevent temporal catastrophe."},"_id":"953f89e8a8a00e49"}
{"name":"Helga - The Red Witch","type":"npc","img":"icons/magic/blood/drop-drip-puddle-red.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":7,"isMainNPC":true,"background":"Helga is a blood witch, centuries old but kept young through blood magic. She guards the southern (red) piece of the Compass Rose and rules the village of Rot through a cult built on blood rituals and mind control. Unlike Margareta's compassion, Helga represents power corrupted over time—she started as a guardian like the other witches but centuries of using blood magic transformed her into a tyrant. She can manipulate any blood she sees, take control of wounded creatures, and heal herself by draining life from others. When she would be killed, she drains nearby blood to regenerate, aging visibly with each use. Her true age is ancient; without blood magic she's a withered crone. The complete Infusion of Purity (with elderberry) can negate her powers. She keeps the village of Rot under her control, with the Porcelain Princess managing her cult and Hammerheads as elite guards. When OZena comes for her piece, Helga captures Dorothea and prepares ritual sacrifice—but this is defensive revenge, not pure evil.","descriptors":["I am centuries-old blood witch kept young by draining life from others","I guard the southern (red) piece of Compass Rose through power and fear","My blood magic lets me control wounds, puppet the bleeding, and regenerate by draining life","I was once a guardian like Margareta but power corrupted me over centuries"],"agenda":["Protect my piece of the Compass Rose from OZena and others","Maintain my cult and power base in Rot","Punish OZena for murdering Johanne and Margareta","Stay young and powerful forever through blood magic","Prevent anyone from learning I can be stopped with Infusion of Purity"],"attributes":{"soma":{"current":3,"max":3},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":0}}},"gifts":[{"name":"Blood Magic","description":"Helga masters three blood magic abilities: **Blood Control** - manipulate any blood she sees to make wounds bleed more (inflict 1 additional Wound), turn spilled blood into sharp projectiles, or create barriers of hardened blood. **Blood Puppet** - once per Scene, take control of any wounded creature within 30 feet (victim resists with Check vs her OL Hard 7). **Blood Healing** - drain blood from nearby sources (servants, animals, pooled blood) to restore 1 Wound by completely draining one human servant.","somaCost":1},{"name":"Blood Witch","description":"Helga has sustained life for centuries through blood magic. When reduced to 0 Wounds, she instead: drains blood from ALL nearby sources, regenerates 1 Wound immediately, ages visibly (gains wrinkles, gray hair, etc.), can do this once per Scene. When killed permanently without blood sources to drain, she rapidly ages centuries in moments and crumbles to dust.","somaCost":0}],"conditions":[],"specialNotes":"Helga is morally complex—defensive against assassin but tyrannical ruler. Voice: commanding, imperious, ancient accent. Gestures: blood swirls when angry. Vulnerability: complete Infusion of Purity (burdock, nettle, hyssop, ELDERBERRY) negates blood magic for one Scene. If spared and freed from blood magic corruption, reveals: Henkle murdered/drove out Griselda; incomplete Compass Rose is incredibly dangerous; Henkle has fortified Smaragd; she can become ally if shown truth. Her red Compass Rose piece: bloodstone needle that pulses like heartbeat, points toward Smaragd. If killed with blood magic active: death triggers blood detonation, everyone in mansion makes Defense Check or takes 1 Wound."},"_id":"57ff8664978dad66"}
{"name":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","type":"npc","img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-triangle-yellow.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":7,"isMainNPC":true,"background":"Margareta Westen is a wealthy noblewoman who was born with a facial deformity that made her an outcast from high society despite her wealth. Rather than become bitter, she used her magic and fortune to create a haven in the village of Gelb where the rejected, disfigured, and diseased could live in peace and dignity. Margareta is one of four witches who formed a coven to protect the Compass Rose by splitting it into four pieces. She holds the western (yellow) piece. Unlike typical fairy tale witches, Margareta and her sisters are guardians trying to prevent the powerful artifact from falling into the wrong hands. They knew that when united, the Compass Rose could summon storms, throw people between worlds, and tear holes in reality. Margareta is genuinely kind—maternal, warm, and compassionate. She welcomes the Hunters to Gelb and explains her mission to provide safety for outcasts. Nearly fifty people with leontiasis, elephantiasis, severe burns, missing limbs, and other disfiguring conditions live in her village without shame. She uses her magic to ease their pain and her wealth to provide for their needs. Her magic focuses on two branches: Emotion Manipulation (she can alter emotional states, making people calm, afraid, angry, or loving) and Telekinesis (moving objects with her mind, including disarming opponents or creating barriers). Despite her power (OL Hard 7), Margareta has only 1 Wound—her compassion and reluctance to harm even those who threaten her is both her greatest strength and her fatal weakness. When OZena comes to kill her and take the Compass Rose piece, Margareta shows compassion even to her would-be murderer, recognizing Dorothea's desperation and suffering.","descriptors":["I am a wealthy noblewoman born with facial deformity who uses magic and fortune to help outcasts","I guard the western (yellow) piece of the Compass Rose to prevent its misuse","My compassion is genuine but makes me vulnerable—I hesitate to harm even enemies","I can manipulate emotions and move objects with my mind"],"agenda":["Protect my village of Gelb and the outcasts who live here in peace","Guard my piece of the Compass Rose from those who would misuse it","Use my magic to ease suffering wherever I find it","Stop OZena before she kills more witches","Show compassion even to those who seek to harm me"],"attributes":{"soma":{"current":3,"max":3},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":0}}},"gifts":[{"name":"Witch - Emotion Manipulation","description":"Margareta can perform a Check to alter the emotional state of anyone she can see within 60 feet. She can make them feel calm (ending rage or panic), afraid (causing them to flee or freeze), angry (turning them hostile to others), or loving (making them trust her or each other). This emotional manipulation lasts for one entire Scene. Victims can resist by making a Check against her Opposition Level (Hard 7). Margareta uses this compassionately—calming frightened villagers, making aggressive visitors peaceful, or helping traumatized people feel love again. But it can also be used tactically in combat.","somaCost":1},{"name":"Witch - Telekinesis","description":"Margareta can move objects with her mind within 60 feet. She can lift and throw items weighing up to 200 pounds. In combat, she can use telekinesis to: disarm opponents by yanking weapons from their hands, create barriers by stacking objects, hurl objects as weapons (treating this as a normal attack Check), pin enemies by dropping heavy items on them, or manipulate the environment to her advantage. Her telekinetic control is precise enough to operate door locks, turn pages, or perform delicate tasks from a distance.","somaCost":1}],"conditions":[],"specialNotes":"Margareta represents the truly good witch—kind, maternal, genuinely helpful. Voice is warm and maternal with slight German accent; touches people gently when speaking; maintains eye contact; smiles despite her facial deformity. Her tragedy: she provides everything the protagonists need (safety, compassion, understanding) but OZena has been manipulated into seeing her as an obstacle. If Margareta survives Part One, she becomes valuable ally: provides information about Compass Rose and other witches; may give Hunters her piece for safekeeping; warns about Helga in Rot and Henkle in Smaragd; can help in final confrontation. If she dies: village of Gelb falls into despair; outcasts may turn hostile blaming Hunters; her death weighs heavily on moral outcome of campaign. Key moment: when confronted by OZena, Margareta shows compassion rather than fighting back, trying to understand Dorothea's suffering. This can be catalyst for OZena's redemption if Hunters intervene. Margareta knows: Johanne was murdered two weeks ago in Schiltach; OZena is being manipulated by Dr. Henkle; Henkle is false wizard in Smaragd; incomplete Compass Rose is incredibly dangerous. Her yellow Compass Rose piece resembles amber needle that hums with energy and points toward Smaragd."},"_id":"af21f6356303f364"}
{"name":"Dose - The Tin Man","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"adversary","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I suffer from leprosy and other diseases","To protect others from contagion, I sealed myself in metal armor","I cannot feel anything through the metal, and I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity piece by piece"],"agenda":["Protect my companions","Find a cure so I can feel again","Prevent myself from becoming a monster"],"gifts":[{"name":"Of Steel","description":"Dose's entire body (except for a small door over his heart) is covered in crude metal armor bolted and strapped onto him. He is immune to all physical attacks unless: 1) An attacker specifically targets the heart door (requires 1 Increment from their Outcome), or 2) An attack is magical or supernatural in nature. When the heart door is opened or targeted, Dose loses this immunity for the rest of the Scene."},{"name":"Giant","description":"Dose has 1 additional Wound beyond what his importance would normally grant."}],"background":"Dose was a patient from early 1900s America who suffered from leprosy and other contagious diseases. To protect others from infection, he sealed himself in crude metal armor bolted and strapped to his body. The armor prevents him from feeling anything—no touch, no warmth, no pain. Over time, Dose has begun to fear he's becoming hollow inside, losing his humanity piece by piece like rust eating away at metal. He was thrown back in time by Dr. Henkle's malfunctioning Compass Rose along with OZena and the others. He follows OZena hoping to find a cure that will allow him to feel again. He helps kidnap Klaus in the swamp to test the Hunters' character.","notes":"ROLEPLAYING:\n- Voice: Muffled and echoing through his helmet\n- Mannerisms: Stiff, mechanical movements; constantly adjusts his armor\n- Pathos: Desperately wants to feel something, anything\n\nWEAKNESS: The small door over his heart is his only vulnerability. Targeting it requires skill (1 Increment from Outcome) but negates his armor immunity for the rest of the Scene.\n\nKEY MOMENT: If the Hunters show Dose compassion, he's deeply moved and may refuse to fight them later. His humanity is the key to his redemption.\n\nDEVELOPMENT: In Part Three of the campaign, he falls in love and his heart returns—metaphorically regaining his lost humanity.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Ozena Part One - The Yellow Village","inspiration":"The Wizard of Oz - Tin Man","role":"Armored companion seeking to regain feeling and humanity","timeDisplaced":true,"originalEra":"Early 1900s America"},"_id":"5197c5bf1f5deb73"}
{"name":"Dose the Tin Man - Original Version","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-metal-orange.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Dose suffers from leprosy and other contagious diseases. To protect others from contamination, he sealed himself in crude metal armor—plates, mail, and sheets bolted and strapped onto his body, covering everything except a small door over his heart. He's a patient from early 1900s America who was displaced through time along with OZena, Lowe, and Hirnloser when Dr. Henkle's incomplete Compass Rose malfunctioned. The metal armor has become both Dose's protection and his prison. He cannot feel anything through the metal—no touch, no warmth, no sensation at all. He fears he is becoming hollow inside, losing his humanity piece by piece, becoming nothing but empty metal shaped like a man. His voice is muffled and echoing through his helmet, his movements stiff and mechanical. In the swamp scene, Dose guards Klaus alongside Hirnloser. His armor makes him nearly invulnerable to physical attacks unless someone specifically targets the small door over his heart (requiring Increment). If the Hunters show Dose compassion or understanding, he's deeply moved—he desperately wants to feel something, anything. This is his ORIGINAL form—by Part Three, he transforms into Dose the Giant in Love when he falls in love with a villager in Smaragd, and his beloved's touch gradually replaces his metal armor with living flesh.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":4,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I suffer from leprosy and sealed myself in metal armor","To protect others from contagion","I cannot feel anything through the metal","I fear I am becoming hollow inside, losing my humanity"],"gifts":[{"name":"Of Steel","description":"Dose's entire body (except for a small door over his heart) is covered in crude metal armor bolted and strapped onto him. He is immune to all physical attacks (swords, arrows, blunt weapons) unless: (1) An attacker specifically targets the heart door, which requires 1 Increment from their Outcome to aim precisely, or (2) An attack is magical or supernatural in nature, which bypasses the physical armor. When the heart door is opened or successfully targeted, Dose loses this immunity for the rest of the Scene as his vulnerability is exposed."},{"name":"Giant","description":"Dose's massive armored form grants him 1 additional Wound beyond what his importance would normally grant (4 total instead of 3 for Main NPC)."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Protect my companions from harm","Find a cure so I can feel again","Prevent myself from becoming a monster","Get home where maybe modern medicine can help me"],"notes":"This is Dose's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Giant in Love in Part Three). Nearly invulnerable to physical attacks except heart door (needs Increment). Magic bypasses armor. Desperately wants to feel something. If shown compassion, deeply moved and may refuse to fight later. Guards Klaus in swamp alongside Hirnloser. Character arc: Hollow metal man → Finds love, armor replaced by flesh. Voice: Muffled, echoing through helmet. Mannerisms: Stiff movements, constantly adjusts armor, clanking sounds. 4 Wounds total due to Giant gift."},"_id":"c8d940897d000993"}
{"name":"Hirnloser - The Scarecrow","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"adversary","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s","The doctors said I was mad, that my brain didn't work right","Now I believe I have no brain at all, but I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface"],"agenda":["Follow OZena because she gives me purpose","Understand the truth of this strange world","Prove I'm more than the madman they say I am"],"gifts":[],"background":"Hirnloser was a psychiatric patient from early 1900s America who was thrown back in time by Dr. Henkle's Compass Rose. The doctors said he was mad, that his brain didn't work right, and over time Hirnloser came to believe he has no brain at all. Despite (or because of) his perceived madness, he sees truths others miss—patterns, connections, and hidden meanings that escape rational minds. He speaks in riddles, rhymes, and fragmented sentences, moving with jerky, unsettling motions. He followed OZena because she gave him purpose when no one else would. He appears at Margareta's village dance and later helps kidnap Klaus to test the Hunters.","notes":"ROLEPLAYING:\n- Speech: Riddles, rhymes, fragmented sentences\n- Mannerisms: Jerky movements, tilts head at odd angles, stares intensely\n- Insight: Despite madness, perceives truths others miss\n\nKEY MOMENT: At the dance, he speaks this riddle: 'The scarecrow sees what you cannot. The tin man feels nothing but knows everything. The lion roars but runs away. And the girl with the silver shoes walks the yellow road to death.'\n\nIf captured, he reveals: 'The wizard in emerald is not what he seems. He steals what he cannot create. The rose blooms red with blood.'\n\nDEVELOPMENT: In Part Three of the campaign, he becomes The Genius when he realizes his mind is his greatest gift.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Ozena Part One - The Yellow Village","inspiration":"The Wizard of Oz - Scarecrow","role":"Mad prophet who sees hidden truths, kidnapper testing the Hunters","timeDisplaced":true,"originalEra":"Early 1900s America"},"_id":"93689be68ae3cc9a"}
{"name":"Hirnloser the Scarecrow - Original Version","type":"npc","img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-ringed-glow-angry-red.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Hirnloser is a psychiatric patient from early 1900s America who was institutionalized for mental illness. The doctors said he was mad, that his brain didn't work right. Over time, Hirnloser internalized this diagnosis and came to believe he has no brain at all—that he's empty-headed like a scarecrow. He was displaced through time along with OZena, Lowe, and Dose when Dr. Henkle's incomplete Compass Rose malfunctioned. Despite his apparent madness, Hirnloser sees things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface, patterns in chaos, connections between events. He speaks constantly in riddles, rhymes, and fragmented sentences, his movements jerky and unsettling. At the village dance in Gelb, he approaches the Hunters and speaks cryptically: 'The scarecrow sees what you cannot. The tin man feels nothing but knows everything. The lion roars but runs away. And the girl with the silver shoes walks the yellow road to death.' In the swamp scene, Hirnloser guards Klaus but can be reasoned with if Hunters show understanding. If captured, he reveals important truths in riddles: 'The wizard in emerald is not what he seems. He steals what he cannot create. The rose blooms red with blood.' This is his ORIGINAL form—by Part Three, he transforms into Hirnloser the Genius when he realizes his mind is his greatest gift.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a psychiatric patient from the early 1900s","The doctors said my brain didn't work right","I believe I have no brain at all, just straw and emptiness","But I see things others cannot—the truth beneath the surface"],"gifts":[{"name":"Mad Insight","description":"Despite (or because of) his madness, Hirnloser perceives truths others miss. Once per Scene, he can ask the Storyteller one question about the current situation and receive a truthful answer, though it will be delivered in riddles or cryptic language. Additionally, Hirnloser cannot be deceived by illusions or lies—he always sees the truth, even if he can't articulate it clearly."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Follow OZena because she gives me purpose","Understand the truth of this strange world","Prove I'm more than the madman they say I am","Protect my companions in my own strange way"],"notes":"This is Hirnloser's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Genius in Part Three). Speaks in riddles/rhymes/fragments. Jerky movements, tilts head oddly, intense stares. Appears at village dance, guards Klaus in swamp. If captured, reveals important clues about Henkle in riddles. Can be reasoned with if shown understanding. Character arc: Madman who thinks he has no brain → Genius who realizes his mind is his weapon. Voice: Fragmented, singsong, cryptic. Mannerisms: Jerky movements, odd angles, dancing steps."},"_id":"6a10d1edcbcceb97"}
{"name":"Lowe the Coward - Original Version","type":"npc","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/cat-hunched-glowing-orange.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"Lowe suffers from leontiasis, a disease that makes his face look like a lion's—a cruel irony given his cowardly nature. He's a patient from early 1900s America who was displaced through time along with Dorothea (OZena), Hirnloser, and Dose when Dr. Henkle's incomplete Compass Rose malfunctioned. Lowe is called a coward because he adapts to survive—he'll side with whoever is winning, never standing firm for any principle. He follows OZena not out of loyalty but because she seems like his best chance of survival and getting home. However, Lowe is actually the most rational of OZena's companions. He questions her increasingly violent methods and fears what they're becoming, but he's too afraid to abandon her. In Part One, Lowe observes the Hunters from a distance, trying to determine if they're allies or threats. If the Hunters show kindness to Henrich and Klaus, Lowe gains respect for them. During the swamp confrontation, he tries to mediate and offers a deal—if the Hunters convince Margareta to give up her Compass Rose piece peacefully, they'll release Klaus unharmed. Lowe wants to avoid unnecessary violence but will fight if cornered. This is his ORIGINAL form—by Part Three, he transforms into Lowe the Brave Fighter when he finds his courage.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I suffer from leontiasis, making my face look like a lion's","People call me a coward because I adapt to survive","I'll side with whoever is winning","I just want to get home alive"],"gifts":[{"name":"Coward's Instinct","description":"Lowe has a supernatural sense for danger and self-preservation. Once per Scene, he can automatically avoid an attack or dangerous situation by fleeing, hiding, or positioning himself safely. Additionally, Lowe always knows which side is winning in a conflict and can switch sides as an action, immediately gaining +1 OL when fighting for the 'winning' side."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Survive and get home to my own time","Protect my companions if it doesn't risk my life","Avoid unnecessary violence","Side with whoever seems most likely to win"],"notes":"This is Lowe's ORIGINAL FORM in Part One (before transformation to Brave Fighter in Part Three). He observes Hunters from distance—if they're kind to Henrich/Klaus, gains respect. Most rational of OZena's companions, questions her violence. In swamp scene, tries to mediate and offer deals. Can be reasoned with more easily than others. Will flee if losing. Character arc: Coward → Brave Fighter. Voice: Hesitant, calculating, defensive. Mannerisms: Checks escape routes, positions near exits, avoids direct confrontation."},"_id":"46aaa535434d6c70"}
{"name":"Lowe the Coward","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"adversary","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I suffer from leontiasis, a disease that makes my face look like a lion's","People call me a coward because I adapt to survive—I'll side with whoever is winning"],"agenda":["Survive and get home to my own time","Protect my companions","Avoid unnecessary violence"],"gifts":[],"background":"Lowe is one of four patients from early 1900s America who were thrown back in time to 1780 by Dr. Henkle's malfunctioning Compass Rose. He suffers from leontiasis, a disease that causes his face to resemble a lion's, earning him the nickname 'the Coward' for his pragmatic approach to survival. Lowe is actually the most rational of OZena's companions—he questions her increasingly violent methods but fears abandoning her, as she represents his only hope of returning home. He observes the Hunters from a distance to judge their character and attempts to mediate conflicts, preferring negotiation over violence.","notes":"Lowe is observing the Hunters during their encounter with Henrich and Klaus. If the Hunters show kindness, he gains respect for them and is more likely to negotiate in the swamp scene. If they attack without trying to negotiate, he becomes convinced they're no better than the witch hunters of this era and fights to the death.\n\nIn the swamp, Lowe offers a deal: if the Hunters convince Margareta to give up her Compass Rose piece peacefully, they'll release Klaus unharmed. This represents his attempt to find a non-violent solution.\n\nDEVELOPMENT: Lowe's character arc involves choosing between loyalty to OZena and doing what's right. His pragmatism could make him an ally if the Hunters show him a better path.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Ozena Part One - The Yellow Village","inspiration":"The Wizard of Oz - Cowardly Lion","role":"Most rational of OZena's companions, attempts mediation","timeDisplaced":true,"originalEra":"Early 1900s America"},"_id":"d57eaf41ab1fae13"}
{"name":"Margareta Westen - The Good Witch","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"adversary","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":7,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a wealthy noblewoman who was born with a facial deformity","Society rejected me, so I use my magic and my fortune to create a haven where the rejected can live in peace and dignity"],"agenda":["Protect my village and the outcasts who live here","Use my magic to ease suffering","Stop OZena before she kills more witches"],"gifts":[{"name":"Witch - Emotion Manipulation","description":"Margareta can perform a Check to alter the emotional state of anyone she can see. She can make them feel calm, afraid, angry, or loving. This lasts for one Scene. Victims can resist with a Check against her Opposition Level."},{"name":"Witch - Telekinesis","description":"Margareta can move objects with her mind. She can lift and throw items weighing up to 200 pounds. In combat, she can use this to disarm opponents, create barriers, or hurl objects as weapons (treating this as a normal attack)."}],"background":"Margareta Westen is the Good Witch of the Yellow Village of Gelb. Born a wealthy noblewoman with a facial deformity, she was rejected by society despite her status. Using her inherited fortune and her magical gifts, she created a haven in the Black Forest where outcasts, the deformed, and the rejected can live in peace and dignity. She provides for their needs and uses her magic to ease their suffering. Margareta holds one piece of the Compass Rose—the Yellow (West) piece—which she guards as part of a coven of four witches who split the artifact to keep it safe. She knows that OZena has already killed Johanne in Schiltach and fears she may be next.","notes":"ROLEPLAYING:\n- Voice: Warm and maternal, with a slight German accent\n- Mannerisms: Touches people gently when speaking to them, maintains eye contact, smiles despite her facial deformity\n- Motivation: Genuinely wants to help outcasts, has built a thriving community\n- Secret: She knows OZena was once a good person driven mad by desperation\n- Weakness: Her compassion makes her vulnerable—she hesitates to harm even those who threaten her\n\nWHAT SHE KNOWS:\n- The Compass Rose is split into four pieces held by four witches\n- Johanne was murdered two weeks ago in Schiltach\n- OZena travels with three companions: Lowe, Hirnloser, and Dose\n- Dr. Henkle is manipulating OZena from Smaragd\n\nHer piece of the Compass Rose resembles a yellow compass needle made of amber that hums with magical energy and points toward Smaragd.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Ozena Part One - The Yellow Village","inspiration":"The Wizard of Oz - Glinda the Good Witch","role":"Target of assassination, protector of outcasts, guardian of Compass Rose piece","compassRosePiece":"West (Yellow)"},"_id":"f2f9d0608b493753"}
{"name":"OZena (Dorothea Gray)","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"adversary","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I suffer from ozena, a disease that destroyed my nose and my life","I was thrown back in time, and the only way home is to gather the pieces of the Compass Rose","I will do whatever it takes to end my suffering—even murder"],"agenda":["Collect all four pieces of the Compass Rose","Get home to my own time","Find a cure for my disease"],"gifts":[{"name":"The Silver Slippers - Short-Range Teleport","description":"Once per Exchange, OZena can teleport up to 30 feet to any location she can see. This doesn't count as an action and can be used to avoid attacks or reposition instantly."},{"name":"The Silver Slippers - Long-Distance Teleport","description":"Once per Scene, OZena can teleport to any location within 1 mile that she has previously visited. This requires her full action. The Silver Slippers are permanently attached to her feet and cannot be removed without killing her."}],"background":"Dorothea Gray grew up in early 1900s America with dreams of becoming a doctor. Her life was destroyed when she contracted ozena—a terrible disease that slowly destroyed her nasal cavity, leaving her face disfigured. Desperate for a cure, she sought out Dr. Norman Henkle, who possessed a partially completed artifact called the Compass Rose. The incomplete artifact malfunctioned, throwing Dorothea and three other patients backward in time to 1780 Germany. Dr. Henkle convinced the desperate Dorothea that four witches held the pieces of the Compass Rose and were evil, and that killing them was necessary to return home. Dorothea became OZena—a killer who has already murdered Johanne in Schiltach. Her face is horribly disfigured, with her nose completely gone. She covers the lower half of her face with a silver mask. She wears enchanted Silver Slippers that allow her to teleport.","notes":"ROLEPLAYING:\n- Voice: Muffled by her mask, tinged with pain and desperation\n- Mannerisms: Keeps one hand on her mask, moves with purpose, eyes constantly scanning\n- Motivation: She was a good person broken by suffering and manipulation\n- Tragedy: Every witch she kills makes her more monstrous, but she's too desperate to stop\n- Redemption: She can be saved if the Hunters show her the truth about Henkle\n\nWHAT SHE KNOWS:\n- Dr. Henkle can send people through time using the Compass Rose\n- The Compass Rose needs all four pieces to function safely\n- She's already killed Johanne and taken the North (Black) piece\n- Henkle told her the witches are evil and must be eliminated\n\nWHAT SHE DOESN'T KNOW:\n- Henkle is lying about the witches being evil\n- The incomplete Compass Rose is more dangerous than helpful\n- Henkle plans to abandon her once he has what he needs\n- Her actions are part of a larger scheme by the One Who Plots in the Shadows","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Ozena Part One - The Yellow Village","inspiration":"The Wizard of Oz - Dorothy","role":"Tragic antagonist hunting witches, can be redeemed","timeDisplaced":true,"originalEra":"Early 1900s America"},"_id":"eb367c5204b878f8"}
{"name":"Dose the Giant in Love - The Transformed Tin Man","type":"npc","img":"icons/magic/life/heart-cross-strong-flame-purple-pink.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Dose was once hollow metal, a tin man feeling nothing, moving mechanically through existence. But during the events in Smaragd, something miraculous happened: he fell in love with a villager of the Emerald Village, and his heart returned. Dose the Giant in Love is undergoing a physical transformation—wherever his beloved touches him, flesh replaces steel. Patches of exposed skin appear on his arms, chest, and face. He moves more fluidly than before, speaks emotionally rather than mechanically, and constantly talks about his beloved. His transformation represents love's power to restore humanity and vulnerability. When the Hunters encounter him, he's torn between loyalty to Henkle (who brought him here) and his desire to protect his beloved. If his beloved is threatened or if the Hunters appeal to his newfound emotions, he can be convinced to stand down or even help. He's protective and emotional rather than the hollow, mechanical being he once was. If he survives the confrontation, Dose chooses to stay in 1780 with his beloved—the Hunters witness the last of his metal armor falling away, leaving him fully human again. Love literally saved his humanity. His story is the most hopeful of the three companions.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I was hollow metal, feeling nothing","But I have fallen in love and my heart has returned","Where love touches, flesh replaces steel","I am becoming human again"],"gifts":[{"name":"Of Steel and Love","description":"Dose's armor is slowly being replaced by living flesh wherever his beloved touches him. **Partial Immunity:** Most of Dose's body still has metal armor covering it, providing immunity to physical attacks (swords, arrows, etc.) except where flesh is exposed. **Vulnerable Heart:** The area around Dose's heart is now flesh, protected only by the small door in his chest. Attacking this spot requires 1 Penalty on the Check but bypasses all armor if successful. **Love's Strength:** When fighting to protect his beloved (if present or threatened), Dose can act twice in one Exchange, his love granting supernatural determination."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Protect my beloved at all costs","Find a way to stay in this time with the one I love","Become fully human again through love's power"],"notes":"Dose's transformation is ongoing and visible—patches of flesh on his arms, chest, face. He speaks constantly about his beloved. If his beloved is present, he's extremely protective. If the Hunters threaten her, he fights to the death. If they protect her or promise to help them stay together, he becomes an ally. He weeps openly when discussing Dorothea's fate. Voice: Emotional, no longer monotone. Mannerisms: Touches the flesh patches, protective gestures. His ending is the happiest—fully human, in love, choosing to stay."},"_id":"b6e211af4ed350c1"}
{"name":"Hirnloser the Genius - The Transformed Scarecrow","type":"npc","img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-ringed-glow-angry-small-teal.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Hirnloser was once mocked as a scarecrow without a brain, speaking in confusing riddles and seeming disconnected from reality. But through the journey with Dorothea (OZena), he has discovered that his mind is his greatest weapon. Hirnloser the Genius now sees patterns others miss and solutions others cannot imagine. His speech is clear, precise, and brilliant—no more riddles, only razor-sharp analysis. He rapidly evaluates situations and proposes tactical solutions, showing pride in his extraordinary intellect. His transformation represents the realization that he was never actually stupid—he simply thought differently, and now he's learned to channel that difference into genius. When the Hunters encounter him in Smaragd, he will be the tactical coordinator for Henkle's defenses (if hostile) or a valuable strategic ally (if convinced of Henkle's betrayal). He carries tools and equipment for every situation, always prepared. If he survives and is redeemed, Hirnloser is furious at being fooled by Henkle and immediately offers his intellect to help stop the doctor. He may choose to stay in 1780 to become a true inventor and scholar, or return to revolutionize early 20th century psychiatry with his insights about the human mind.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["They said I had no brain, but I have discovered my genius","I see patterns others miss, solutions others cannot imagine","I am no scarecrow—I am a master tactician","My mind is my greatest weapon"],"gifts":[{"name":"Genius","description":"Hirnloser has realized his intellect is extraordinary. **Tactical Insight:** Once per Scene, Hirnloser can describe a brilliant tactic or plan that automatically succeeds (no Check required)—positioning advantage, environmental exploitation, perfect timing, etc. **Countermeasure:** Three times per Scene, Hirnloser can prevent a Hunter from activating a Gift by explaining exactly how to counter it, forcing them to use a different approach. **Prepared:** Hirnloser always has the right tool, item, or piece of information for the current situation—he's thought ahead and prepared contingencies."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Prove that intelligence can overcome any obstacle","Protect my companions with superior planning","Never be fooled or manipulated again"],"notes":"Hirnloser's transformation means he no longer speaks in riddles—his communication is crystal clear and often intimidatingly intelligent. If shown evidence of Henkle's manipulation, he becomes furious at being fooled and turns his genius against the doctor. He coordinates with Lowe and Dose as a tactical unit. Voice: Clear, precise, academic. Mannerisms: Adjusts spectacles, constantly calculating. If redeemed, becomes an invaluable ally with his strategic mind."},"_id":"00bda0f1987e548b"}
{"name":"Lowe the Brave Fighter - The Transformed Coward","type":"npc","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/cat-hunched-glowing-red.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"Lowe was once called a coward—a lion-faced man who adapted to whoever seemed to be winning, never standing firm for anything. But through his journey with Dorothea (OZena) and the trials they faced, Lowe has undergone a dramatic transformation. He has found his courage and embraced true heroism. Now Lowe the Brave Fighter stands firm when others flee, speaks with confidence, and meets eyes directly. He no longer adapts to the winning side—he has chosen his loyalty (to Henkle or to the Hunters depending on Dorothea's fate and how the previous scenarios concluded) and defends it without wavering. His transformation represents the completion of a character arc, from cowardly opportunist to genuine hero. When the Hunters encounter him in Smaragd, he will either stand as their enemy (defending Henkle) or as a potential ally (if Dorothea vouched for them or if he's been shown evidence of Henkle's betrayal). His presence is commanding and his newfound courage is infectious to allies around him. If he survives the confrontation and is redeemed, Lowe thanks the Hunters for showing him that courage isn't the absence of fear—it's acting despite it. He may become a Hunter himself or return to his own time to live boldly.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I was called a coward, but I have found my courage","I am a lion-faced warrior who stands firm when others flee","I will protect those I care about, no matter the cost","My loyalty is chosen, not purchased"],"gifts":[{"name":"Hero","description":"Lowe has overcome his cowardice and embraced heroism. **Fearless:** Immune to fear effects and mind control attempts. **Inspiring Presence:** Allied NPCs within 30 feet gain +1 to their Opposition Level when fighting alongside Lowe. **Last Stand:** When reduced to 0 Wounds, Lowe can take one final dramatic action before falling unconscious (attack, speech, or helping an ally)."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Defend those I've chosen to protect","Prove that courage can be found, not just born with","Stand firm regardless of who seems to be winning"],"notes":"Lowe's transformation is complete—he no longer exhibits cowardly behavior. If shown evidence of Henkle's betrayal, he turns against the doctor immediately, heartbroken but resolute. He works well with Hirnloser and Dose as a coordinated team. Voice: Strong and confident, no longer hesitant. Mannerisms: Direct eye contact, protective stance. If redeemed, he offers to help the Hunters in future scenarios."},"_id":"f7a5f2063aa26b20"}
{"name":"Porcelain Princess - The Disfigured Noblewoman","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-white-blue.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"The Porcelain Princess appears as a beautiful woman wearing an elaborate porcelain mask and elegant gown, but beneath the mask, her face is hideously disfigured by disease. She was once a noblewoman who society rejected after illness destroyed her beauty. In desperation, she sought out Helga and accepted the witch's offer: power and purpose in exchange for eternal service. Now she manages Helga's cult in the village of Rot, organizing blood rituals and maintaining order among the mind-controlled villagers. She is surrounded by her Porcelain Dolls—twelve masked servants carrying various weapons who stand perfectly still until commanded. The Princess knows why the Hunters have come and offers them three choices: leave now and Helga will spare OZena (a lie), join the cult and receive Helga's blessing (eternal servitude), or try to rescue OZena and die in the attempt. If the Hunters refuse her deal, she signals her Dolls to attack. If defeated and spared, she may remove her mask voluntarily, revealing her disfigurement and explaining how Helga's promises of beauty were lies. She possesses a key to Helga's mansion and a vial of glowing blood, gasping when defeated: 'You fools... you've doomed her. Helga will drink OZena's blood before you reach her!'","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I was a noblewoman disfigured by disease","Society rejected me, so I embraced Helga's offer","Power in exchange for service","I manage her cult and keep the villagers in line"],"gifts":[{"name":"Cult Leader","description":"The Porcelain Princess commands the Porcelain Dolls with perfect coordination. As long as she lives and can see them, the Dolls act with +1 OL when following her direct commands. She can command all twelve Dolls to move as a single coordinated unit, creating tactical advantages in combat. If she's killed or incapacitated, the Dolls become disoriented and act independently at their base OL."}],"conditions":[],"notes":"The Porcelain Princess holds the key to Helga's mansion and knows the ritual schedule. If the Infusion of Purity is used on her, she's freed from blood magic control and may become an ally, revealing the truth about Helga's corruption. She carries a vial of blood that glows—this is OZena's blood, being prepared for the ritual. The Princess genuinely believed Helga would restore her beauty but has been betrayed like all of Helga's servants."},"_id":"4ab85a9cb2eeabd6"}
{"name":"The Hammerheads - Elite Guards","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-barbute-banded-steel.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"The Hammerheads are Helga's elite guards, warriors who wear massive hammer-shaped helmets that extend down to completely cover their heads and chests. These specially designed helmets provide incredible protection for the upper body but leave the lower body vulnerable. The Hammerheads are blood-bound servants like the Porcelain Dolls, mind-controlled by Helga's magic and forced to serve as her personal bodyguards. They work in pairs with coordinated tactics: one engages directly while the other flanks, using their heavy helmets as weapons by headbutting opponents. They protect Helga fanatically, willing to die for her without hesitation. The only way to damage a Hammerhead is to specifically target their lower body (legs, abdomen), which requires accepting 1 Penalty on the attack Check, or to use magic and area attacks that don't require precise targeting. If the Infusion of Purity breaks Helga's blood magic control over them, they immediately stop fighting and flee in confusion. Beneath the helmets are ordinary soldiers from nearby towns, kidnapped and enslaved by Helga's cult. Some have been serving for years, completely losing their original identities. The helmets are works of craftsmanship—heavy iron shaped like massive hammers, with eye slits and breathing holes, weighing over 40 pounds. Only the strongest warriors can wear them in combat.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["We are Helga's elite guards","Warriors who wear massive hammer-shaped helmets","Our helmets protect our heads and torsos completely","We serve the Red Witch without question"],"gifts":[{"name":"Hammerhead Helmet","description":"The Hammerheads wear specially designed helmets that extend down to cover their heads and chests completely. **Head/Chest Immunity:** Attacks targeting the head or chest automatically miss or deal no damage. **Vulnerable Lower Body:** Attackers can target the lower body (legs, abdomen), but this requires 1 Penalty on the attack Check. Magic or area attacks that don't require precise targeting bypass this protection. The helmet can also be used as a battering weapon for headbutt attacks."}],"conditions":[],"notes":"Hammerheads typically work in pairs: one engages directly while the other flanks. They use coordinated tactics and their helmets to headbutt opponents. They protect Helga fanatically in her mansion. If the Infusion breaks Helga's control, they stop fighting and flee. There are usually 4-6 Hammerheads guarding Helga's ritual chamber. Smart players will target their legs or use magic to bypass the helmet protection. The helmets make them slow but nearly invulnerable from the waist up."},"_id":"e0ea0339d36db049"}
{"name":"Elizaveta - The Cruel Bride","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/female.svg","flags":{},"token":{"name":"Elizaveta","img":"icons/svg/female.svg"},"system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"wounds":{"max":3,"current":3,"extra":0},"soma":{"max":0,"current":0},"xp":0,"background":"Elizaveta enjoys a life of comfort and prestige, secured through calculated manipulation and cold ambition. She is determined to protect her position, even if it means sacrificing her own daughter to keep secrets buried.","descriptors":["I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever is needed to get what I want."],"gifts":[],"agenda":"To maintain the comforts and luxuries I have earned. That means ridding myself of my annoying daughter Iskra.","conditions":[],"notes":"She is the mother of Iskra and the central antagonist behind the girl's tragic backstory."},"_id":"91103ca25d7868a7"}
{"name":"Gerard Dubois the Incapable Noble","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","flags":{},"token":{"name":"Gerard Dubois","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"},"system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":3,"wounds":{"max":1,"current":1,"extra":0},"soma":{"max":0,"current":0},"xp":0,"background":"Gerard Dubois is the current baron of Durfort, a position inherited from his renowned father. Though he postures with authority, his reputation pales in comparison to the legacy of the man who came before him.","descriptors":["I am the noble baron of Durfort and my word is law. I live in the shadow of my late father’s glory."],"gifts":[],"agenda":"Put an end to the menacing werewolves and cover up any possible mischief.","conditions":[],"notes":"Gerard relies heavily on others to act in his name, particularly Vincent Arn and the town guards."},"_id":"604900e3b6fe83cb"}
{"name":"Vincent Arn - Former Huntsman and Chief of the Guards","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/guard.svg","flags":{},"token":{"name":"Vincent Arn","img":"icons/svg/guard.svg"},"system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"wounds":{"max":3,"current":3,"extra":0},"soma":{"max":0,"current":0},"xp":0,"background":"Vincent Arn served as a huntsman before climbing the ranks to become the chief of the guards under Gerard Dubois. Though loyal in appearance, he has aligned himself with Elizaveta for personal gain.","descriptors":["I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms about doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life without working so hard."],"gifts":["Veteran: Vincent is skilled in taking advantage of any situation. When he has the support of at least two allies, he gains 1 Additional Success to Position Checks. If he is supported by at least three of his men, every action against him receives 1 Penalty and Vincent can inflict 1 additional Wound."],"agenda":"I understand how the world works and who really runs the Dubois household. Pleasing Elizaveta is the best way to maintain my status.","conditions":[],"notes":"Vincent leads the guards and is an extension of Elizaveta’s will. He is an experienced and dangerous obstacle."},"_id":"5aed8a0ba66bb5c1"}
{"name":"Saint Demetrius - The Guardian","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-crystal-blue.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"Saint Demetrius is one of Saint George's six Paladins, renowned for his unwavering dedication to protecting his companions. He places the defense of his allies before his own life, embodying the ideal of selfless service. Demetrius is the shield of the Paladin group—always positioned to intercept attacks meant for others, always ready to throw himself in harm's way. His Gift allows him to take wounds in place of his allies, and when he does so, his Opposition Level increases as his protective fury grows. This makes him increasingly dangerous the more he sacrifices himself. In combat, Demetrius positions himself between enemies and his fellow Paladins, particularly protecting Saint George himself. Smart Hunters can exploit this—by threatening his allies, they can force Demetrius to take multiple wounds, potentially taking him out of the fight while he tries to save everyone. However, this also makes him more dangerous with each wound taken. Demetrius is utterly devoted to his duty and sees no greater honor than dying to protect those he serves. He views the Hunters as threats to his brothers and sisters in faith, and will not hesitate to interpose himself between them and any Paladin—especially if Saint Martha is threatened, as she represents compassion within the group.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a Paladin in service of Saint George","His word, for me, is law","Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales","I put the defense of my companions before my own life"],"gifts":[{"name":"Paladin - Guardian","description":"Once per Exchange, Demetrius can take 1 Wound in place of one of his allies (must be within 30 feet and line of sight). When he does this, he increases his Opposition Level by 1 for the rest of the Scene (cumulative—if he takes wounds multiple Scenes, the bonuses stack). This makes him progressively more dangerous as he sacrifices himself. The wound transfer happens automatically if Demetrius chooses—the ally takes no damage, and Demetrius takes the full wound instead."}],"conditions":[],"notes":"Demetrius is Paladin #2 (roll 1d6 to determine which appears). His protective nature can be exploited—threaten his allies to force him to take wounds, potentially eliminating him while making him more dangerous. He always positions between enemies and allies, especially protecting Saint Martha. Works best with other Paladins as he has allies to protect. If isolated, loses much of his effectiveness. Can't be reasoned with—duty and protection are absolute. Voice: Calm and resolute, reassuring to allies. Mannerisms: Shield raised, defensive stance, watches for threats to allies."},"_id":"ffe92fe2cca5170a"}
{"name":"Saint Margaret - The Ambitious","type":"npc","img":"icons/weapons/polearms/spear-hooked-gold.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"Saint Margaret is one of Saint George's six Paladins, but unlike the others who serve out of devotion or duty, Margaret serves out of ambition. She wants to affirm her role in the Church and ultimately overthrow 'that arrogant Saint George' to take his position. This secret agenda makes her simultaneously the most dangerous and the most exploitable of the Paladins. Margaret's Gift makes her stronger the more Saint George is weakened—her Opposition Level increases by 1 for each Wound Saint George has suffered, and she can take an immediate additional action whenever Saint George takes damage. This means that in prolonged battles where Saint George is being worn down, Margaret becomes progressively more powerful, potentially even surpassing her master. She fights with extra vigor when Saint George is threatened, not out of loyalty, but because his suffering empowers her. Margaret is brilliant, ruthless, and calculating. She's playing a long game, waiting for the perfect moment to make her move against Saint George. Smart Hunters can exploit this in multiple ways: they might make a deal with Margaret to betray Saint George in exchange for helping her achieve her ambitions, they might reveal her treachery to Saint George to sow discord among the Paladins, or they might deliberately wound Saint George to make Margaret more powerful and uncontrollable, forcing the other Paladins to deal with her. Of all the Paladins, Margaret is the most likely to make a deal with the Hunters—but she's also the least trustworthy, as her ambition outweighs any sense of honor or loyalty.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a Paladin in service of Saint George","His word, for me, is law","Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales","I want to affirm my role in the Church and overthrow that arrogant Saint George"],"gifts":[{"name":"Paladin - Ambition","description":"Margaret increases her Opposition Level by 1 for each Wound that Saint George has suffered (if Saint George has 2 Wounds, Margaret's OL becomes 7). Once per Scene, when Saint George suffers 1 Wound, Margaret can immediately perform 1 additional action as she seizes the opportunity. This makes Margaret progressively more dangerous as battles wear on and Saint George is weakened, potentially making her more powerful than her master by the end of a prolonged fight."}],"conditions":[],"notes":"Margaret is Paladin #6 (roll 1d6 to determine). MOST DANGEROUS in prolonged battles—gains +1 OL per Saint George Wound, bonus action when he's hurt. Secret ambition to overthrow Saint George makes her exploitable: can make deals with Hunters, reveal her treachery to cause Paladin discord, or deliberately empower her by wounding Saint George to make her uncontrollable. Most likely to negotiate with Hunters but LEAST trustworthy—ambition trumps honor. Brilliant, ruthless, calculating. Voice: Smooth, confident, hints of superiority. Mannerisms: Watches Saint George constantly, smiles when he's wounded, calculates constantly."},"_id":"803dfd6ae796a11c"}
{"name":"Saint Martha - The Friendly","type":"npc","img":"icons/magic/holy/angel-winged-humanoid-blue.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"Saint Martha is one of Saint George's six Paladins, and she stands apart from the others in a crucial way: she does not believe that Broken Tales should be eradicated, only understood. This compassionate perspective makes her the conscience of the Paladin group and a potential ally for Hunters who can reach her. Martha believes there's a difference between monsters who choose evil and those who are simply misunderstood or corrupted against their will. She joined Saint George's Paladins hoping to protect innocents and bring understanding between humans and the supernatural, not to wage war. When Saint George initiates a Witch Hunt against the Hunters, Martha secretly doubts his judgment—especially if she's witnessed the Hunters performing good deeds or showing mercy. Her Gift makes Hunters reluctant to attack her (receiving 2 Penalties if other Paladins are available as targets), representing both her non-threatening demeanor and the moral difficulty of striking someone who radiates compassion. Smart Hunters will recognize Martha as the key to ending the Witch Hunt peacefully. If they can show her evidence of Saint George's manipulation, or demonstrate through their actions that they're genuinely trying to help people, Martha may be convinced to speak on their behalf or even actively assist them. She's the Paladin most likely to betray Saint George if convinced he's wrong—not out of treachery, but out of a higher loyalty to true justice and compassion.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a Paladin in service of Saint George","His word, for me, is law","Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales","I do not think Broken Tales should be eradicated, only understood"],"gifts":[{"name":"Paladin - Friendly","description":"Any Hunter who acts against Martha when there are other Paladins as potential targets will receive 2 Penalties on their action. This represents both Martha's non-threatening demeanor that makes it psychologically difficult to attack her, and her positioning that makes her a harder target when allies are nearby. This only applies when at least one other Paladin is present and available as a target—if Martha is isolated, she loses this protection."}],"conditions":[],"notes":"Martha is Paladin #4 (roll 1d6 to determine). KEY CHARACTER for peaceful resolution—she doubts Saint George's Witch Hunt and can be convinced to help Hunters. Shows compassion, believes in understanding rather than destruction. If shown evidence of manipulation or witnesses Hunters' good deeds, may speak for them or actively assist. Protected by Gift when with other Paladins (2 Penalties to attack her). Most likely to betray Saint George out of higher loyalty to justice. Can be the bridge to redemption. Voice: Gentle, questioning, compassionate. Mannerisms: Hesitates before violence, shows concern for all parties."},"_id":"cef97c2135814811"}
{"name":"Saint Syrus - The Veteran","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-bascinet-reinforced.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"Saint Syrus is the oldest of Saint George's six Paladins, a grizzled veteran who has fought Broken Tales for decades. His experience has taught him to trust only his own judgment, making him both incredibly effective and frustratingly stubborn. Syrus has seen countless supernatural threats, studied their patterns, and developed countermeasures for virtually every type of Gift or magical ability. His vast experience allows him to negate the effect of a Hunter's Gift once per Scene—he always seems to know exactly how to counter whatever supernatural ability is being used. This makes him a particularly dangerous opponent for Hunters who rely heavily on their Gifts. When a Hunter activates a powerful Gift expecting it to turn the tide of battle, Syrus calmly explains the countermeasure he's prepared and nullifies it entirely. However, Syrus's reliance on his own judgment is also his weakness. He's set in his ways, dismissive of new ideas or approaches he hasn't personally validated. He won't listen to Martha's doubts or Trebizond's questions—he's fought monsters for decades and knows what they are. This stubbornness means he's unlikely to be convinced that Saint George is wrong, but it also means he can be outmaneuvered by tactics he hasn't encountered before. Hunters who use creative or unconventional approaches may catch him off-guard, as his experience becomes a liability when facing something genuinely new.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a Paladin in service of Saint George","His word, for me, is law","Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales","I am the oldest of the Paladins and I only trust my own judgment"],"gifts":[{"name":"Paladin - Veteran","description":"Once per Scene, Syrus can negate the effect of a Gift activated by a Hunter. The Saint will find a method to counter Gifts, drawn from his great experience—he might interrupt a ritual, throw holy water to disrupt magic, use a specific ward he's prepared, or simply know the weakness of that particular ability. When he does this, the Hunter's Gift activates but has no effect, and any Soma or resources spent are still consumed. This makes Syrus extremely dangerous to Hunters who rely on one powerful Gift as their primary strategy."}],"conditions":[],"notes":"Syrus is Paladin #5 (roll 1d6 to determine). Most dangerous to Gift-reliant Hunters—can negate one Gift per Scene. Has countermeasures for almost everything due to decades of experience. Stubborn and dismissive of others' judgment—won't listen to Martha or Trebizond's doubts. Unlikely to be convinced Saint George is wrong. Weakness: set in his ways, can be outmaneuvered by truly creative/unconventional tactics he hasn't seen before. Experience becomes liability against novel approaches. Voice: Gruff, dismissive, authoritative. Mannerisms: Crosses arms, shakes head at others' suggestions, prepared stance."},"_id":"604f6687dc16b44f"}
{"name":"Saint Theodore - The Furious","type":"npc","img":"icons/weapons/axes/axe-double-engraved-red.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"Saint Theodore is one of Saint George's six Paladins, and he is consumed by the ecstasy of battle. For Theodore, combat is the sweetest of pleasures—a religious experience that brings him closer to divine purpose. His fury in battle makes him one of the most dangerous Paladins. Theodore always inflicts additional wounds when he strikes, and even successful Defense Checks cannot fully protect against his rage-fueled attacks. The only way to avoid his bonus damage is to spend an Increment to nullify it. In combat, Theodore is aggressive and relentless, seeking out the strongest opponents and engaging them with wild abandon. He laughs during battle, quotes scripture with fervor, and treats each exchange of blows as a sacrament. Unlike Demetrius who protects, or Martha who shows compassion, Theodore exists to destroy those Saint George has deemed enemies. His weakness is his predictability—his love of battle means he can be baited, manipulated into charging, or separated from his fellow Paladins by appealing to his desire for glorious combat. However, underestimating Theodore is fatal. He's an expert warrior whose fury is backed by years of training. He views the Hunters as worthy opponents—monsters who will provide him with the greatest battle of his life. Smart Hunters will find ways to neutralize him without engaging in direct combat, as facing him head-on plays to his greatest strength.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a Paladin in service of Saint George","His word, for me, is law","Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales","The ecstasy of battle is for me the sweetest of pleasures"],"gifts":[{"name":"Paladin - Furious","description":"Theodore always inflicts 1 Additional Wound when raging against an enemy. He still inflicts 1 Wound even if the Defense Check is a successful Outcome. The only way to avoid the effect of this Gift is to spend an Increment to cancel the Wound. This means Theodore is guaranteed to deal at least 1 Wound on every attack unless the defender has Increment available. When he achieves a successful attack normally, he deals 2 Wounds total (1 base + 1 from Furious)."}],"conditions":[],"notes":"Theodore is Paladin #3 (roll 1d6 to determine). Most dangerous in direct combat—ALWAYS deals at least 1 Wound unless Increment spent. Predictable due to battle-lust: can be baited, separated, or manipulated into charging. Laughs during combat, quotes scripture fervently, treats battle as sacrament. Seeks strongest opponents. Avoid engaging him directly if possible—neutralize through environment, traps, or forcing him to waste attacks on obstacles. Voice: Loud, passionate, laughs frequently. Mannerisms: Aggressive stance, eager movements, grins during combat."},"_id":"9ceea6d2b449f2e0"}
{"name":"Trebizond - Princess of a Distant Country","type":"npc","img":"icons/weapons/thrown/net-weighted-purple.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"biography":"Trebizond is a princess from a distant country who serves as one of Saint George's six Paladins. She brings an exotic perspective and arsenal to the Paladins, using unfamiliar weapons and objects from her homeland that surprise and confound opponents. Unlike some of the more rigid Paladins, Trebizond possesses an unshakeable curiosity about new things—a trait that can be both her strength and her weakness. She's fascinated by the cultures and peoples she encounters during her travels with Saint George, and this curiosity sometimes distracts her from her holy mission. Her special equipment includes items like Magic-Finding Dust that reveals hidden enchantments, whips as sharp as blades that can strike from distance, exotic poisons that induce specific effects, or mechanical devices from her homeland that seem almost magical. When she creates a special equipment Descriptor and uses it, her Opposition Level increases to 6, making her a formidable combatant. Smart Hunters can exploit her curiosity—offering to show her something unique or fascinating might distract her or even make her question Saint George's absolute judgments. Of all the Paladins, she's the most likely to be swayed by experiencing something that challenges her worldview.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a Paladin in service of Saint George","His word, for me, is law","Years of training made me adept at fighting Broken Tales","Sometimes I am seized by unshakeable curiosity about new things"],"gifts":[{"name":"Paladin - From a Far Country","description":"Trebizond can make use of exotic weapons and objects to surprise opponents. Once per Scene, she can create a Descriptor that represents special equipment, such as 'Magic-Finding Dust' or 'A Whip as Sharp as a Blade' or 'Poison from the Eastern Lands' or 'Mechanical Crossbow of My Homeland'. When using her special equipment, Trebizond increases her Opposition Level by 1 (to 6). The equipment lasts for the Scene and provides tactical advantages beyond just the OL bonus."}],"conditions":[],"notes":"Trebizond is Paladin #1 (roll 1d6 to determine which Paladin appears). Her curiosity is both strength and weakness—she might be distracted by fascinating objects or stories, or convinced to question orders if shown something truly unique. She works well with other Paladins but sometimes pursues her own interests. Can be separated from group by exploiting her curiosity. Voice: Accented, expressive, asks many questions. Mannerisms: Examines everything closely, touches unfamiliar objects."},"_id":"3b29a65e043830a3"}
{"_id":"ArthurBrowne","name":"Arthur Browne - The Big Brother","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-bull-horned-orange.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as the mastermind of the gang","Living in my natural prison has taught me how to see even in total darkness"],"agenda":"Take revenge on Bardolf for corrupting everything I built in Whitehaven and regain control of the city / Transforming all the inhabitants of Whitehaven into Pig Heads","gifts":[{"name":"The Flesh of The God Under the Mine","description":"Arthur can tear pieces of flesh from the God's head to harness its powers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes a Spawn of the God and begins to grow disgustingly, engaging all nearby enemies. Arthur can tear one piece of meat off per action, up to a maximum of 3."},{"name":"Gang Leader","description":"Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength."}],"background":"Arthur Browne worked for years to make Whitehaven a quiet town where every resident could have a home and a job. When Bardolf Greed bought the town's favor, he seized property and leveled houses to build factories, throwing the three Browne brothers out on the street. Arthur was forced to work in the mines, where a collapse left him trapped by falling rubble and left for dead. The collapse was caused by the awakening of The God Under the Mine. Alive and trapped underground, Arthur found the God's head and after days of agony fed on divine flesh, discovering it confers incredible powers. Consumed with grief and wild hope, his brother Frank dug a tunnel to create communication. United in vengeance and endowed with the power of divine flesh, the three brothers began their personal war against Bardolf Greed, leading the Pig Heads gang from beneath the city."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"city-of-pigs","role":"main-antagonist","location":"cave-under-mine"}}
{"_id":"ClarenceBrowne","name":"Clarence Browne - The Younger Brother","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-scream-tan.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am the youngest of the Pig Heads","Despite believing in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on it","From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back of my hand"],"agenda":"Having fun and lazing around all day, carrying on the Pig Head's cause in my spare time","gifts":[{"name":"Slacker","description":"Clarence is a master of the art of disappearing when things get tough. In the presence of even a small crowd, Clarence can leave a Scene when it is his turn to act, without anything or anyone being able to stop him. When using this Gift, Clarence hides in the orchard, passing the entire following Scene there."},{"name":"Gang Leader","description":"Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength."}],"background":"The youngest of the three Browne brothers. When Bardolf Greed threw them out on the street and forced them to accept jobs as miners or starve, Clarence soon quit, choosing the life of a slacker over labor in the mines. After the mine collapse that injured Frank and trapped Arthur, Clarence became part of the Pig Heads revolution but maintains his lazy lifestyle. He lives in a rickety rundown house with a thatched roof in the abandoned apple orchard that the Browne family once gifted to the city. Clarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take them off guard. When the mutation from eating the God's flesh begins to take effect on miners, Clarence approaches the targets, offering them the opportunity to join the gang. He has a special relationship with Emma, his childhood friend, who he has always promised to take away from Whitehaven, though she knows he will never abandon his brothers. From hanging around the city, Clarence knows Whitehaven like the back of his hand."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"city-of-pigs","role":"recruiter-scout","location":"orchard"}}
{"_id":"FrankBrowne","name":"Frank Browne - The Middle Brother","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/hand/gauntlet-tooled-purple.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":4,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act as the strongarm of the gang","I have control over all cultists","The power of The God Under the Mine has given me strength and endurance equal to that of five men"],"agenda":"Take revenge on Bardolf for what he did to me and find a remedy for the wounds that have marred me since the day of the accident / Mix the flesh of The God Under the Mine with beef from the slaughterhouse and feed it to the miners to add to the ranks of the gang","gifts":[{"name":"The Pincer","description":"Frank replaced his left arm with a home-made mechanical arm with many functions. During a Scene, Frank can use each of the following one time: 1. Crush, a hit with the pincer inflicts 1 additional Wound; 2. Pulley, the pincer can launch from the arm and raise or lower Frank about thirty feet. Frank can carry 2 other subjects with him."},{"name":"Gang Leader","description":"Eating the flesh of The God Under the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a single action where they can harness their superhuman strength."}],"background":"The middle Browne brother who lost an arm and a leg during the mine collapse that awakened The God Under the Mine and left Arthur trapped. Consuming with grief and driven by wild hope that Arthur wasn't dead, Frank dug a long vertical tunnel, eventually managing to create a communication channel with his brother. United in vengeance and endowed with the power of divine flesh, the three brothers began their personal war against Bardolf Greed. Frank has managed to get hired as a butcher at the big meat factory in the city and secretly mixes the flesh of the God with common meat, infecting the unsuspecting miners who eat it. When the mutation begins to take effect, Clarence approaches the targets, offering them the opportunity to join the gang. Frank replaced his missing arm with a home-made mechanical pincer with multiple functions. He takes care of their elderly mother Martha but tells her nothing of their plans."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"city-of-pigs","role":"lieutenant-infiltrator","location":"slaughterhouse"}}
{"name":"Father Adrien","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"adversary","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a young priest who chose to take holy vows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and distillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life."],"agenda":["Accumulate wealth through absinthe smuggling and then flee across the ocean to rebuild my life in the new world"],"gifts":[],"background":"A young priest at the church of Saint Pierre in Paris who appears tired and worried, with swollen eyes from lack of sleep. Adrien distills absinthe in his church cellars and smuggles it through the catacombs. He murdered little Yvonne when she discovered his illegal laboratory - he strangled her unconscious, set her on fire, and threw her remains in the catacombs. Now haunted by nightmares of Yvonne's death and visions of Paris burning. Yvonne's spirit is systematically killing all those who witnessed her death but stayed silent, saving Adrien for last. A heavy trap door connects the cellars to the catacombs where he passes absinthe to his henchmen (the Ravens).","notes":"The main antagonist whose crime started everything. Will call the Hunters to investigate, hoping they stop Yvonne before she reaches him. If confronted, will collapse in tears and reveal his recurring nightmares. Knows about the comet Morituris and fears the New Year.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"The Smile in the Darkness","inspiration":"The Little Match Girl (Hans Christian Andersen)","role":"Main Antagonist - Murderer Priest"},"_id":"665c8d7ef099b582"}
{"name":"The Gallant Knight","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-great-masked-brown.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"biography":"The Gallant Knight is a respected and experienced warrior of the kingdom, whose skill is matched only by his honor. He was one of the knights sent by the King and Queen to rescue Princess Tuvstarr from the corrupted forest. Unlike his brothers-in-arms who perished in the wilderness, the Gallant Knight successfully navigated the dangers, retrieved Tuvstarr's crown and dress, reached the black pond at the heart of the forest, and dove through its freezing waters to enter the Dream World. There he found Princess Tuvstarr in her paradise of eternal summer. He tried to bring her back, but the innocent child offered him something he had never experienced: a world without pain, without aging, without duty. In the Dream World, the Knight's old wounds stopped hurting, his grey hair began to darken, and the weight of years lifted from his shoulders. Faced with this temptation and Tuvstarr's pure innocence, he abandoned his quest and vowed to remain as her eternal protector. Now he sits under a tree in perfect sunshine, eating an apple, his sword beside him—a warrior who chose paradise over duty. But somewhere deep in his heart, guilt gnaws at him, knowing his brothers died searching while he abandoned them. He can be convinced to resume his quest if shown the two-tailed fox crest of his fallen comrades and told of their deaths, or if the Hunters appeal to his honor and sense of duty.","attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a respected and experienced knight of the kingdom","My skill is only matched by my honor","I have abandoned my quest for paradise","I struggle with guilt over my fallen brothers"],"gifts":[{"name":"Gallant Knight","description":"The Knight is incredibly skilled in combat, but his honor prevents him from using his full abilities against those he doesn't consider truly evil. **Defensive Mastery:** When defending against an enemy attack, his exceptional skill increases his Opposition Level by +1. **Merciful Strike:** The Knight will never inflict the final Wound on a target if he doesn't feel it truly deserves death. Against opponents he doesn't consider evil (like the Hunters), he will fight defensively and disarm rather than kill. **Honorable Combat:** Against truly evil foes, the Knight fights without restraint and can be devastating."}],"conditions":[],"agenda":["Protect Princess Tuvstarr from any threats in this perfect world","Enjoy this paradise free from pain, aging, and duty","Silence the voice in my heart that says I betrayed my oath and my brothers"],"notes":"The Gallant Knight represents the temptation of paradise and the conflict between duty and desire. Voice: Warm, nostalgic, with undertones of guilt. Encounter: Sits under tree eating apple in Dream World, sword beside him, appears younger and healthier than he should be. Can be convinced to help: 1) Show him the two-tailed fox crest from fallen knight's body and tell him all his brothers died searching. 2) Appeal to his honor and knightly vows. 3) Remind him of the corruption spreading in the real world. If convinced, he'll reveal Tuvstarr's location and help persuade her to leave. If Hunters possess the Lance of the Fallen Knight, he'll ask them to return it to the castle in the real world as proof of his brothers' sacrifice. In combat, fights defensively against Hunters (doesn't want to kill them) but can be defeated. His fall from duty is tragic—he's not evil, just tired and seduced by comfort. Successfully convincing him is key to peaceful resolution with Tuvstarr."},"_id":"2a60541a45465aa7"}
{"_id":"HattaCarter","name":"Hatta Carter - The Mad Inventor","type":"npc","img":"icons/equipment/head/top-hat-brown-striped.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my time","My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings and aggressiveness"],"agenda":"I want the company of witty people and not cold automata. I long for the chats I had with Alice","gifts":[{"name":"Time Clocks","description":"Hatta can manipulate one of his clocks to influence time:\n\n1. Slow: Once per Scene, Hatta increases his OL by 2 when defending against a threat.\n\n2. Speed Up: Once per Scene, Hatta and one of his Automata can act, immediately stopping anyone's action regardless of the situation in the narrative. If an Automaton has already acted, it can act again thanks to this Gift."}],"background":"Hatta Carter is the most skilled inventor in all of England, famous for his theories on automatons. Alice Liddell hired him to research Wonder and make sense of the physics-defying nature of the asylum. Thanks to his hard work, the structure now responds to Alice's will, becoming a place from which it is impossible to escape without her consent. However, Alice has imprisoned the mad inventor in the Basement, keeping him alive for future bedlam expansion projects. Driven to madness by loneliness, Hatta has built two Automata (a Rabbit and a Lizard) as pretend tea companions."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"wonderbedlam","role":"imprisoned-inventor","location":"basement","companions":["rabbit-automaton","lizard-automaton"]}}
{"_id":"LizardAutomaton","name":"Lizard Automaton","type":"npc","img":"icons/creatures/magical/construct-iron-stomping-green.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter","Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions at the same time"],"gifts":[{"name":"Tail","description":"The Automaton always acts twice, once with its front legs and once with its long tail, but cannot focus both its actions on the same target."}],"background":"The second automaton built by Hatta Carter during his imprisonment in the Basement of Wonder. Created as a companion for lonely tea parties, this mechanical lizard is equipped with a powerful tail that allows it to perform multiple actions simultaneously. More robust than its Rabbit counterpart, it serves as both companion and guardian to the mad inventor."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"wonderbedlam","role":"automaton-guardian","creator":"hatta-carter","location":"basement"}}
{"_id":"RabbitAutomaton","name":"Rabbit Automaton","type":"npc","img":"icons/creatures/magical/construct-iron-stomping-yellow.webp","system":{"npcType":"adversary","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":false,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":2,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am an automaton in the service of Hatta Carter","Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible jumps and crush everything when landing"],"gifts":[{"name":"Leap","description":"When it acts, the Automaton can free itself from any engagement with ease by jumping away. If it lands on a victim, it increases its OL by 1 for the attack and if it inflicts 1 Wound, the target will also be knocked to the ground."}],"background":"One of two automatons built by Hatta Carter during his imprisonment in the Basement of Wonder. Created out of loneliness to serve as a pretend tea companion, this mechanical rabbit is equipped with powerful legs that allow it to make devastating leaps. It serves its creator faithfully, defending him from any who would disturb his solitude."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"wonderbedlam","role":"automaton-guardian","creator":"hatta-carter","location":"basement"}}